  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      CP-675,206 (tremelimumab) is a fully humanized monoclonal antibody that binds to activated T
      lymphocytes and by enhancing their activation may produce a stimulation of the immune
      response against tumoral or viral antigens. In this clinical trial, the ability of
      tremelimumab to produce tumor responses among hepatitis C virus-infected patients with
      hepatocellular carcinoma not amenable to other therapies will be explored. Besides, the
      effect on the replication of the virus will be analysed.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
